						<div class="postbody">Just play a game and let us know how it looks on your computer monitor as compared to playing an emulator (this way any lag of your LCD will affect the emulator too, and not cause a difference). Do this for the preview, and also for recording. How much lag for the preview? The old PowerMac I use has composite video input, and the on-screen preview looks good and doesn't have any noticeable lag, for example. It's very useful to have video input, so you don't need a TV on your desk when doing NES development.</div>

