				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It wasn't a question of whether the video capture lagged by a couple of frames; it was whether it lags by tens or hundreds of frames, as some people have mentioned some video capture devices do. I would always expect a lag of a few frames at minimum with a video input device, and wouldn't use it if I wanted to play the NES. The main use is during development, where you're seeing if something works right, and where a lag of one second would be really annoying, but 5 frames wouldn't. At least that's how I use video input.</div>

